        "created_at": "2025-03-31T00:27:17.248Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I would like to revisit the topic ‚ÄúFont Styling for Signal messages‚Äù i.e. support for <strong>bold</strong>, <em>italics</em>, and such. There is a (long!) thread <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/font-styling-for-signal-messages/612\">here</a> which is now closed/locked when the feature graduated to beta last year.</p>\n<p>I very much would like to have this!</p>\n<p>But if I read the source code in the github repo‚Äôs correctl has been reverted? Can anyone share what happened? It certainly looks like something that is achievable? I would like to contribute time/code to a working solution if it would help</p>",
